.TH AUTOSUGGEST 1 "2026-06-16" "autosuggest-cli 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
autosuggest \- context-aware CLI autosuggestion engine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B autosuggest
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B autosuggest
launches the interactive autosuggestion shell with ghost-text predictions,
Tab/Shift-Tab completion cycling, and next-step workflow suggestions.
On first run it automatically starts the telemetry daemon and performs
any necessary data migration.
.PP
The suggestion engine uses frecency scoring (frequency + exponential recency
decay) combined with directory-context weighting to rank historical commands.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-daemon
Run the telemetry daemon in the foreground. Intended for use with systemd
or other service managers.
.TP
.B \-\-daemon\-bg
Start the daemon in the background and exit immediately.
.TP
.B \-\-status
Print the current daemon status (running/stopped, PID, socket path).
.TP
.B \-\-stop
Stop the running daemon.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.B \-h\fR, \fB\-\-help
Show usage information and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_DATA_HOME/autosuggest/history.db
Command history database (default: ~/.local/share/autosuggest/history.db).
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/autosuggest/workflows.yaml
User workflow rules (default: ~/.config/autosuggest/workflows.yaml).
Falls back to the bundled workflows.yaml shipped with the package.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/autosuggest.sock
Unix domain socket for daemon IPC.
.TP
.I $XDG_RUNTIME_DIR/autosuggest.pid
Daemon PID file.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Base directory for user data files (default: ~/.local/share).
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for user configuration (default: ~/.config).
.TP
.B XDG_RUNTIME_DIR
Base directory for runtime files (sockets, PIDs). Falls back to
/tmp/autosuggest-$UID if unset.
.SH INTERACTIVE SHELL
.TP
.B Right Arrow
Accept ghost-text suggestion.
.TP
.B Tab / Shift-Tab
Cycle through completion menu.
.TP
.B 1, 2, 3
Accept numbered next-step suggestion.
.TP
.B Ctrl-D
Exit the shell.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR suggest\-hook (1),
.BR suggest\-import (1),
.BR suggest\-stats (1)
